data.enText: until now; until the particular time you are talking about

data.chText: 迄今仍属未知种类的蛾
data.enText: a hitherto unknown species of moth

tr: used in negative statement to describe a situation that has existed up to this point or up to the present time

value.def: You use hitherto to indicate that something was true up until the time you are talking about, although it may no longer be the case.

example.ex: The polytechnics have hitherto been at an unfair disadvantage in competing for pupils and money...
example.tran: 到目前为止，理工专科学校在争取生源和资金方面一直处于劣势。

example.ex: Hitherto, the main emphasis has been on the need to resist aggression...
example.tran: 迄今为止，一直重点强调的是要抵抗侵略。

example.ex: The helicopter is the first in the world to be designed to serve three hitherto very distinct markets.
example.tran: 这款直升机是世界上首批为满足3个迄今为止完全不同的市场而设计的机型。

gramarinfo.label: ADV after v, ADV with cl, ADV adj/-ed
